Anonymous Fri 24 Sep 2021 17:49:05 No.41872535 Report

>>41871728
Just to get this out of the way at the beginning, I'm not criticizing you, Frite.
I'm just as guilty of thinking line this from time to time.

I dislike the 'in between' phrase. You and I know that means more about reflection, recovering, or internal/personal conflict.
But the inexperienced writer that has absolutely no outline makes it a filler episode, and usually not a good one that means something to the overarching plot.
I find them hard for a different reason. Because they're slower paced, there's more setup for future events going on. That means more chances for your characters to take an axe to your established outline.
My experience is that I can't tell if my setups in chapters like this was successful until things come due.

I still love writing them because it's where a character (especially a popular one like Tigress!) can go from nothing to professional heart string tougher.
Keep your head up and take it bird by bird
